headlines.title: Tyrese Haliburton, Pacers bench carry Indiana to NBA Finals Game 3 win vs. Thunder
headlines.description: The All-Star guard had his best game of the NBA Finals, and reserve Bennedict Mathurin scored a game-high 27 for underdog Indiana.

headlines.title: Spending Review 'renewing Britain' or 'reckless splurge'
headlines.description: Reaction to the chancellor's Spending Review dominates the front pages on Thursday.

headlines.title: Trump-China deal, Thailand CPI
headlines.description: Asia-Pacific markets traded mixed as traders assessed U.S. President Donald Trump's declaration that a trade deal with China was "done."

headlines.title: Walmart says this is its highest paying job, not including managers
headlines.description: Walmart decorates over 150,000 cakes a week. The company says they employ 6,000 cake decorators across the nation.

headlines.title: Red Sox To Acquire Jorge Alcala
headlines.description: The Red Sox and Twins are getting together on a trade that will send some relief help to Boston. Read more at MLB Trade Rumors.

headlines.title: Yankees Considering Starts For Ben Rice At Catcher
headlines.description: With Giancarlo Stanton nearing a return, the Yankees are considering giving Ben Rice a look behind the plate. Read more at MLBTR.

headlines.title: Chicago Braces For Surge In Immigration Raids As Mayor Brandon Johnson Urges City To 'Resist'
headlines.description: The mayor's chief of staff said federal agents received notice to deploy to five Democrat-led cities, including Chicago — where recent actions have already drawn thousands to the streets in protest.

headlines.title: South Korea halts anti-North Korea loudspeaker broadcasts to ease tensions
headlines.description: South Korea’s military has shut down loudspeakers broadcasting anti-North Korean propaganda along the inter-Korean border. It's a move aimed at easing tensions.

headlines.title: A Forgotten Cancer Is Surging in Young People, And Experts Are Puzzled
headlines.description: Appendix cancer is a condition that, until recently, was so rare that most people never gave it a second thought.

headlines.title: Judge rules Trump administration cannot continue to detain Palestinian activist Mahmoud Khalil
headlines.description: The judge is staying his injunction until Friday to allow the Department of Homeland Security time to appeal the decision.
